included.description:
Served as the lead UX architect on ford.com and user experience subject matter expert for the Ford North America customer experience team. 

Operationalized a customer lifecycle framework, developed journey maps, and utilized research insights and foresights to prioritize experiences that matter to key customer segments. 

Integrated a global UX design system on ford.com to meet the needs of users and satisfy business goals in North American markets. 

Led UX design for in-dealer digital innovations.
included.title: User Experience Lead, Ford North America

included.description:
Support the Experience Architecture program and its faculty through advising and relationship building with other industry organizations and professionals. 

Facilitate supplemental design and research instruction, providing a "real world" perspective on the practice of user experience design.

Mentor undergraduate and graduate Experience Architecture students with a focus on how best they can prepare themselves for careers in user experience.
included.title: Experience Architect in Residence

included.description:
Developing a user experience strategy practice for global product development that leverages human-centered generative research, lean/iterative UX design discovery, and customer validation to inform product prioritization and strategic design decisions for feature sets within and beyond the vehicle.

Champion and facilitator of organizational strategic planning for the User Experience department at General Motors.
included.title: User Experience Strategy Lead

included.description:
Ideated, designed, and validated automotive infotainment innovations for Jaguar Land Rover and Intel, delivering customer and market insights to drive use case development, product prioritization, and experience visioning. 

Conducted field research and insight analysis, and defined strategic design direction for "quantified self" data analysis software.
included.title: User Experience Designer

included.description:
Designed and documented the next generation cockpit experience for Cadillac vehicles, with a focus on the infotainment system framework and audio, connectivity, and comfort experiences.

Planned, moderated, and synthesized design research to inform iterative design decisions for new and carryover feature sets.

Researched and developed organizational design strategies to optimize user experience capabilities within the product development function at GM.
included.title: Senior User Experience Designer
